I'm Evelin, a computer and cognitive science student @ [Occidental College](https://www.oxy.edu). 

I currently work as a research assistant @ Occidental's Human-Computer Interaction Lab, where I apply motion capture technology (MOCOPI) to sign language acquisition and real-time visual feedback systems. The end goal is to build interactive software that helps second-language learners acquire sign language!

This upcoming Fall semester, I will be an Artificial Intelligence Intern @ [Accuro Technology S.I.](https://www.accuro.es/) in Madrid, Spain for my semester abroad. I'll partner with clients, primarily in Spanish, to design technology solutions aligned with business goals, leveraging machine learning and blockchain/Web3 (smart contracts, decentralized identity, dApps).

Outside of school, I continously follow the advancement of science and how different scientificical fields intereact with tech. I'm also interested in [Charrería](https://ich.unesco.org/en/RL/charreria-equestrian-tradition-in-mexico-01108), horticulture, and soccer. 

